      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on comparative study against LES reference data for centrifugal pump flows (Nicoud et al. 2011); SST outperformed k-ε and RSM for near-wall shear prediction. Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis power-law selected after systematic comparison of four constitutive models against 12 independent experimental datasets. Model form uncertainty quantified via Bayesian model averaging (BMA) over the four hemolysis models; BMA posterior weight for Giersiepen–Wurzinger = 0.61. Model form uncertainty contribution: 28% of total NIH variance.",
